The Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) has, however, described the list as an interim report.From the 4.4 million signatures the BBI team presented, the commission has weeded out a staggering three million names from the list. President Uhuru Kenyatta and ODM leader Raila Odinga are among the estimated three million names missing from those verified as having backed the Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) Bill. 

The Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) has, however, described the list as an interim report, with the possibility of another list being published with some more names.   



