ODM leader Raila Odinga wants the process to go on as fast as possible. 

“After the IEBC has verified signatures, we will go to the county assemblies. And we hope that we can get 24 county assemblies to approve within one week. And, thereafter, we will go to Parliament. From there, we will go to the people of Kenya,” Mr Odinga explained recently. 

He went on: “Now, these other people should say their stand. And then the people of Kenya will decide. And whatever they decide, we will accept it. That is how democracy works.” The new changes appear to placate key constituencies that are instrumental to the passage of the Bill. An overwhelming number has come out in support of the BBI report, says the ODM party leader. He was held at the Kileleshwa police station in Nairobi. Development comes months after Talai Council of Elders crowned DP to lead the community.